{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Most people don't know that when I went to high school in this country --"},{"time":4000,"text":"I applied for university at a time when I was convinced"},{"time":8000,"text":"I was going to be an artist and be a sculptor."},{"time":10000,"text":"And I came from a very privileged background. I was very lucky."},{"time":13000,"text":"My family was wealthy, and my father believed in one thing,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and that was to give us all as much education as we wanted."},{"time":21000,"text":"And I announced I wanted to be a sculptor in Paris."},{"time":23000,"text":"And he was a clever man. He sort of said,"},{"time":25000,"text":"\"Well, that's OK, but you've done very well in your math SATs.\""},{"time":29000,"text":"In fact, I'd got an 800. And he thought I did very well -- and I did, too -- in the arts:"},{"time":34000,"text":"this was my passion."},{"time":37000,"text":"And he said \"If you go to MIT,\" to which I had been given early admission,"},{"time":40000,"text":"\"I will pay for every year you're at MIT,"},{"time":44000,"text":"in graduate or undergraduate -- as much as you want --"},{"time":46000,"text":"I will pay for an equal number of years for you to live in Paris.\""},{"time":49000,"text":"And I thought that was the best deal in town, so I accepted it immediately."},{"time":53000,"text":"And I decided that if I was good in art, and I was good in mathematics,"},{"time":56000,"text":"I'd study architecture, which was the blending of the two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59000,"text":"I went and told my headmaster that, at prep school."},{"time":62000,"text":"And I said to him what I was doing, that I was going to go study architecture"},{"time":67000,"text":"because it was art and mathematics put together."},{"time":71000,"text":"He said to me something that just went completely over my head."},{"time":75000,"text":"He said, \"You know, I like grey suits, and I like pin-striped suits,"},{"time":80000,"text":"but I don't like grey pin-striped suits.\""},{"time":84000,"text":"And I thought, \"What a turkey this guy is,\" and I went off to MIT."},{"time":88000,"text":"I studied architecture, then did a second degree in architecture,"},{"time":91000,"text":"and then actually quickly realized that it wasn't architecture."},{"time":97000,"text":"That really, the mixing of art and science was computers,"},{"time":102000,"text":"and that that really was the place to bring both, and enjoyed a career doing that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106000,"text":"And probably, if I were to fill out Jim Citrin's scale,"},{"time":112000,"text":"I'd put 100 percent on the side of the equation"},{"time":116000,"text":"where you spend time making it possible for others to be creative."},{"time":121000,"text":"And after doing this for a long time, and the Media Lab passing the baton on,"},{"time":126000,"text":"I thought, \"Well, maybe it's time for me to do a project."},{"time":128000,"text":"Something that would be important, but also something"},{"time":132000,"text":"that would take advantage of all of these privileges that one had.\""},{"time":136000,"text":"And in the case of the Media Lab, knowing a lot of people,"},{"time":139000,"text":"knowing people who were either executives or wealthy,"},{"time":144000,"text":"and also not having, in my own case, a career to worry about anymore."},{"time":149000,"text":"My career, I mean, I'd done my career."},{"time":151000,"text":"Didn't have to worry about earning money."},{"time":153000,"text":"Didn't have to worry about what people thought about me."},{"time":156000,"text":"And I said, \"Boy, let's really do something that takes advantage of all these features,\""},{"time":162000,"text":"and thought that if we could address education, by leveraging the children,"},{"time":166000,"text":"and bringing to the world the access of the computers,"},{"time":170000,"text":"that that was really the thing we should do."},{"time":174000,"text":"Never shown this picture before, and probably going to be sued for it."},{"time":177000,"text":"It's taken at three o'clock in the morning, without the permission of the company."},{"time":179000,"text":"It's about two weeks old. There they are, folks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"If you look at the picture, you'll see they're stacked up."},{"time":188000,"text":"Those are conveyor belts that go around."},{"time":191000,"text":"This is one of the conveyor belts with the thing going by,"},{"time":194000,"text":"but then you'll see the ones up above."},{"time":197000,"text":"What happens is, they burn into flash memory the software,"},{"time":202000,"text":"and then test them for a few hours."},{"time":205000,"text":"But you've got to have the thing moving on the assembly line, because it's constant."},{"time":209000,"text":"So they go around in this loop, which is why you see them up there."},{"time":213000,"text":"So this was great for us because it was a real turning point. But it goes back."},{"time":217000,"text":"This picture was taken in 1982, just before the IBM PC was even announced."},{"time":222000,"text":"Seymour Papert and I were bringing computers to schools"},{"time":225000,"text":"and developing nations at a time when it was way ahead of itself."},{"time":228000,"text":"But one thing we learned was that these kids can absolutely jump into it"},{"time":234000,"text":"just the same way as our kids do here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237000,"text":"And when people tell me, \"Who's going to teach the teachers to teach the kids?\""},{"time":240000,"text":"I say to myself, \"What planet do you come from?\""},{"time":243000,"text":"Okay, there's not a person in this room -- I don't care how techie you are --"},{"time":246000,"text":"there's not a person in this room that doesn't give their laptop or cell phone to a kid"},{"time":251000,"text":"to help them debug it. OK?"},{"time":253000,"text":"We all need help, even those of us who are very seasoned."},{"time":258000,"text":"This picture of Seymour -- 25 years ago. Seymour made a very simple"},{"time":263000,"text":"observation in 1968, and then basically presented it in 1970 --"},{"time":268000,"text":"April 11 to be precise -- called \"Teaching Children Thinking.\""},{"time":271000,"text":"What he observed was that kids who write computer programs"},{"time":275000,"text":"understand things differently, and when they debug the programs,"},{"time":279000,"text":"they come the closest to learning about learning."},{"time":282000,"text":"That was very important, and in some sense, we've lost that."},{"time":286000,"text":"Kids don't program enough and boy,"},{"time":288000,"text":"if there's anything I hope this brings back, it's programming to kids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292000,"text":"It's really important. Using applications is OK,"},{"time":296000,"text":"but programming is absolutely fundamental."},{"time":299000,"text":"This is being launched with three languages in it: Squeak, Logo, and"},{"time":303000,"text":"a third, that I've never even seen before."},{"time":305000,"text":"The point being, this is going to be very, very intensive on the programming side."},{"time":308000,"text":"This photograph is very important because it's much later."},{"time":312000,"text":"This is in the early 2000s. My son, Dimitri -- who's here,"},{"time":317000,"text":"many of you know Dimitri -- went to Cambodia, set up this school"},{"time":321000,"text":"that we had built, just as the school connected it to the Internet."},{"time":324000,"text":"And these kids had their laptops. But it was really what spirited this,"},{"time":330000,"text":"plus the influence of Joe and others. We started One Laptop per Child."},{"time":334000,"text":"This is the same village in Cambodia, just a couple of months ago."},{"time":339000,"text":"These kids are real pros. There were just 7,000 machines out there"},{"time":343000,"text":"being tested by kids. Being a nonprofit is absolutely fundamental."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"Everybody advised me not to be a nonprofit, but they were all wrong."},{"time":353000,"text":"And the reason being a nonprofit is important is actually twofold."},{"time":357000,"text":"There are many reasons, but the two that merit the little bit of time is:"},{"time":360000,"text":"one, the clarity of purpose is there. The moral purpose is clear."},{"time":365000,"text":"I can see any head of state, any executive I want, at any time, because"},{"time":369000,"text":"I'm not selling laptops. OK? I have no shareholders."},{"time":373000,"text":"Whether we sell, it doesn't make any difference whatsoever."},{"time":376000,"text":"The clarity of purpose is absolutely critical. And the second is very counterintuitive --"},{"time":382000,"text":"you can get the best people in the world."},{"time":385000,"text":"If you look at our professional services, including search firms,"},{"time":389000,"text":"including communications, including legal services, including banking,"},{"time":393000,"text":"they're all pro bono. And it's not to save money."},{"time":397000,"text":"We've got money in the bank. It's because you get the best people."},{"time":400000,"text":"You get the people who are doing it because they believe in the mission,"},{"time":403000,"text":"and they're the best people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405000,"text":"We couldn't afford to hire a CFO. We put out a job description for a CFO at zero salary,"},{"time":410000,"text":"and we had a queue of people."},{"time":413000,"text":"It allows you to team up with people. The U.N.'s not going to be"},{"time":416000,"text":"our partner if we're profit making. So announcing this with Kofi Annan"},{"time":419000,"text":"was very important, and the U.N. allowed us"},{"time":422000,"text":"to basically reach all the countries. And this was the machine we were showing"},{"time":428000,"text":"before I met Yves Behar."},{"time":430000,"text":"And while this machine in some sense is silly,"},{"time":434000,"text":"in retrospect, it actually served a very important purpose."},{"time":436000,"text":"That pencil-yellow crank was remembered by everybody."},{"time":441000,"text":"Everybody remembered the pencil-yellow crank. It's different."},{"time":444000,"text":"It was getting its power in a different way. It's kind of childlike."},{"time":447000,"text":"Even though this wasn't the direction we went because the crank --"},{"time":451000,"text":"it really is stupid to have it on board, by the way."},{"time":453000,"text":"In spite of what some people in the press don't get it, didn't understand it,"},{"time":456000,"text":"we didn't take it off because we didn't want to do --"},{"time":460000,"text":"having it on the laptop itself is really not what you want."},{"time":463000,"text":"You want a separate thing, like the AC adaptor."},{"time":466000,"text":"I didn't bring one with me, but they really work much better off-board."},{"time":470000,"text":"And then, I could tell you lots about the laptop, but I decided on just four things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475000,"text":"Just keep in mind -- because there are other people, including Bill Gates,"},{"time":479000,"text":"who said, \"Gee, you've got a real computer.\""},{"time":482000,"text":"That computer is unlike anything you've had, and does things --"},{"time":485000,"text":"there are four of them --"},{"time":487000,"text":"that you don't come close to. And it's very important to be low power,"},{"time":490000,"text":"and I hope that's picked up more by the industry."},{"time":493000,"text":"That the reason that you want to be below two watts is"},{"time":496000,"text":"that's roughly what you can generate with your upper body."},{"time":499000,"text":"Dual-mode display -- that sunlight display's fantastic."},{"time":501000,"text":"We were using it at lunch today in the sunlight, and the more sunlight the better."},{"time":504000,"text":"And that was really critical. The mesh network, it'll become commonplace."},{"time":508000,"text":"And of course, \"rugged\" goes without saying."},{"time":511000,"text":"And the reason I think design matters isn't because I wanted to go to art school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514000,"text":"And by the way, when I graduated from MIT,"},{"time":517000,"text":"I thought the worst and silliest thing to do would be to go to Paris for six years. (Laughter)"},{"time":520000,"text":"So, I didn't do that. But design matters for a number of reasons."},{"time":524000,"text":"The most important being that it is the best way to make an inexpensive product."},{"time":528000,"text":"Most people make inexpensive products by taking cheap design,"},{"time":532000,"text":"cheap labor, cheap components, and making a cheap laptop."},{"time":536000,"text":"And, in English, the word \"cheap\" has"},{"time":539000,"text":"a double meaning, which is really appropriate,"},{"time":542000,"text":"because it's cheap, in the pejorative sense, as well as inexpensive."},{"time":546000,"text":"But if you take a different approach, and you think of very large-scale integration,"},{"time":550000,"text":"very advanced materials, very advanced manufacturing --"},{"time":553000,"text":"so you're pouring chemicals in one end, iPods are spewing out the other --"},{"time":555000,"text":"and really cool design, that's what we wanted to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559000,"text":"And I can race through these and save a lot of time because"},{"time":561000,"text":"Yves and I obviously didn't compare notes."},{"time":564000,"text":"These are his slides, and so I don't have to talk about them."},{"time":568000,"text":"But it was really, to us, very important as a strategy."},{"time":574000,"text":"It wasn't just to kind of make it cute, because somebody --"},{"time":578000,"text":"you know, good design is very important."},{"time":580000,"text":"Yves showed one of the power-generating devices."},{"time":585000,"text":"The mesh network, the reason I -- and I won't go into it in great detail --"},{"time":590000,"text":"but when we deliver laptops to kids in the remotest and poorest parts of the world,"},{"time":593000,"text":"they're connected. There's not just laptops."},{"time":596000,"text":"And so, we have to drop in satellite dishes. We put in generators."},{"time":599000,"text":"It's a lot of stuff that goes behind these. These can talk to each other."},{"time":602000,"text":"If you're in a desert, they can talk to each other about two kilometers apart."},{"time":606000,"text":"If you're in the jungle, it's about 500 meters. So if a kid bicycles home,"},{"time":610000,"text":"or walks a few miles, they're going to be off the grid, so to speak."},{"time":613000,"text":"They're not going to be near another laptop,"},{"time":616000,"text":"so you have to nail these onto a tree, and sort of, get it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619000,"text":"You don't call Verizon or Sprint. You build your own network."},{"time":623000,"text":"And that's very important, the user interface."},{"time":626000,"text":"We are launching with 18 keyboards. English is by far the minority."},{"time":630000,"text":"Latin is relatively rare, too. You just look at some of the languages."},{"time":633000,"text":"I'm willing to suspect some of you hadn't even heard of them before."},{"time":637000,"text":"Is there anybody in the room, one person, unless you work with OLPC,"},{"time":642000,"text":"is there anybody in the room that can tell me what language"},{"time":645000,"text":"the keyboard is that's on the screen? There's only one hand -- so you get it."},{"time":651000,"text":"Yes, you're right. He's right. It's Amharic,"},{"time":655000,"text":"it's Ethiopian. In Ethiopia, there's never been a keyboard."},{"time":658000,"text":"There is no keyboard standard because there's no market."},{"time":661000,"text":"And this is the big difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664000,"text":"Again, when you're a nonprofit, you look at children as a mission, not as a market."},{"time":667000,"text":"So we went to Ethiopia, and we helped them make a keyboard."},{"time":671000,"text":"And this will become the standard Ethiopian keyboard."},{"time":674000,"text":"So what I want to end with is sort of what we're doing to roll it out."},{"time":677000,"text":"And we changed strategy completely. I decided at the beginning --"},{"time":680000,"text":"it was a pretty good thing to decide in the beginning,"},{"time":683000,"text":"it's not what we're doing now -- is to go to six countries."},{"time":686000,"text":"Big countries, one of them is not so big, but it's rich."},{"time":689000,"text":"Here's the six. We went to the six,"},{"time":692000,"text":"and in each case the head of state said he would do it, he'd do a million."},{"time":695000,"text":"In the case of Gaddafi, he'd do 1.2 million, and that they would launch it."},{"time":699000,"text":"We thought, this is exactly the right strategy, get it out,"},{"time":703000,"text":"and then the little countries could sort of piggyback on these big countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705000,"text":"And so I went to each of those countries"},{"time":708000,"text":"at least six times, met with the head of state probably two or three times."},{"time":711000,"text":"In each case, got the ministers, went through a lot of the stuff."},{"time":714000,"text":"This was a period in my life where I was traveling 330 days per year."},{"time":717000,"text":"Not something you'd envy or want to do."},{"time":720000,"text":"In the case of Libya, it was a lot of fun meeting Gaddafi in his tent."},{"time":725000,"text":"The camel smells were unbelievable."},{"time":728000,"text":"And it was 45 degrees C. I mean, this was not"},{"time":732000,"text":"what you'd call a cool experience. And former countries --"},{"time":736000,"text":"I say former, because none of them really came through this summer --"},{"time":738000,"text":"there was a big difference between getting a head of state"},{"time":742000,"text":"to have a photo opportunity, make a press release."},{"time":744000,"text":"So we went to smaller ones. Uruguay, bless their hearts."},{"time":747000,"text":"Small country, not so rich. President said he'd do it, and guess what?"},{"time":750000,"text":"He did do it. The tender had nothing in it that related to us,"},{"time":754000,"text":"nothing specific about sunlight-readable, mesh-network, low-power,"},{"time":757000,"text":"but just a vanilla laptop proposal."},{"time":760000,"text":"And guess what? We won it hands down."},{"time":762000,"text":"When it was announced that they were going to do every child in Uruguay,"},{"time":766000,"text":"the first 100,000, boom, went to OLPC."},{"time":768000,"text":"The next day -- the next day, not even 24 hours had passed -- in Peru,"},{"time":771000,"text":"the president of Peru said, \"We'll do 250.\" And boom, a little domino effect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774000,"text":"The president of Rwanda stepped in and said he would do it."},{"time":777000,"text":"The president of Ethiopia said he would do it."},{"time":780000,"text":"And boom, boom, boom. The president of Mongolia."},{"time":782000,"text":"And so what happens is, these things start to happen with these countries --"},{"time":785000,"text":"still not enough."},{"time":787000,"text":"Add up all those countries, it didn't quite get to thing, so we said,"},{"time":792000,"text":"\"Let's start a program in the United States.\" So, end of August, early September,"},{"time":797000,"text":"we decide to do this. We announced it near the middle, end --"},{"time":800000,"text":"just when the Clinton Initiative was taking place."},{"time":803000,"text":"We thought that was a good time to announce it."},{"time":805000,"text":"Launched it on the 12 of November."},{"time":808000,"text":"We said it would be just for a short period until the 26. We've extended it until the 31."},{"time":813000,"text":"And the \"Give One, Get One\" program is really important because"},{"time":817000,"text":"it got a lot of people absolutely interested."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822000,"text":"The first day it was just wild. And then we said,"},{"time":827000,"text":"\"Well, let's get people to give many. Not just one, and get one,"},{"time":831000,"text":"but maybe give 100, give 1,000.\" And that's where you come in."},{"time":835000,"text":"And that's where I think it's very important. I don't want you all to go out and"},{"time":838000,"text":"buy 400 dollars worth of laptops. Okay? Do it, but that's not going to help. Okay?"},{"time":844000,"text":"If everybody in this room goes out tonight and orders one of these things for 400 dollars,"},{"time":847000,"text":"whatever it is, 300 people in the room doing it -- yeah, great."},{"time":851000,"text":"I want you do something else."},{"time":854000,"text":"And it's not to go out and buy 100 or 1,000, though,"},{"time":857000,"text":"I invite you to do that, and 10,000 would be even better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860000,"text":"Tell people about it! It's got to become viral, OK?"},{"time":864000,"text":"Use your mailing lists. People in this room have extraordinary mailing lists."},{"time":869000,"text":"Get your friends to give one, get one."},{"time":872000,"text":"And if each one of you sends it to 300 or 400 people, that would be fantastic."},{"time":876000,"text":"I won't dwell on the pricing at all."},{"time":879000,"text":"Just to say that when you do the \"Give One, Get One,\""},{"time":882000,"text":"a lot of press is a bit about, \"They didn't make it, it's 188 dollars, it's not 100.\""},{"time":887000,"text":"It will be 100 in two years. It will go below 100."},{"time":891000,"text":"We've pledged not to add features, but to bring that price down."},{"time":895000,"text":"But it was the countries that wanted it to go up, and"},{"time":898000,"text":"we let them push it up for all sorts of reasons. So what you can do --"},{"time":901000,"text":"I've just said it. Don't just give one, get one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904000,"text":"I just want to end with one last one. This one is not even"},{"time":906000,"text":"24-hours old, or maybe it's 24-hours."},{"time":909000,"text":"The first kids got their laptops. They got them by ship,"},{"time":913000,"text":"and I'm talking now about 7,000, 8,000 at a time went out this week."},{"time":916000,"text":"They went to Uruguay, Peru, Mexico."},{"time":921000,"text":"And it's been slow coming, and we're only making about 5,000 a week,"},{"time":925000,"text":"but we hope, we hope, sometime in next year,"},{"time":930000,"text":"maybe by the middle of the year,"},{"time":932000,"text":"to hit a million a month. Now put that number,"},{"time":936000,"text":"and a million isn't so much. It's not a big number."},{"time":938000,"text":"We're selling a billion cell phones worldwide this year."},{"time":941000,"text":"But a million a month in laptop-land is a big number."},{"time":944000,"text":"And the world production today, everybody combined, making laptops,"},{"time":948000,"text":"is five million a month. So I'm standing here telling you that sometime next year,"},{"time":952000,"text":"we're going to make 20 percent of the world production."},{"time":955000,"text":"And if we do that, there are going to be a lot of lucky kids out there."},{"time":959000,"text":"And we hope if you have EG two years from now,"},{"time":963000,"text":"or whenever you have it again,"},{"time":965000,"text":"I won't have bad breath, and I will be invited back,"},{"time":969000,"text":"and will have, hopefully by then, maybe 100 million out there to children."},{"time":972000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":973000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}